4A1.25 1.25 0 0 0 2.75 9v9A1.25 1.25 0 0 0 4 19.25h16A1.25 1.25 0 0 0 21.25 18V9A1.25 1.25 0 0 0 20 7.75h-1.997a2.751 2.751 0 0 1-2.42-1.443l-.486-.9a1.25 1.25 0 0 0-1.1-.657h-3.993Z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg></div></div></div><span class=" useView-module__vOh_Ha__view Text-module__KIh4Sq__text Text-module__KIh4Sq__multiline _sdz_tertiary-text" style="--Text--font-family: inherit; --Text--font-size: var(--font-size-default); --Text--line-height: var(--line-height-default); --Text--color: var(--foreground-dimmest);">2 actions</span></button></div><div class=" useView-module__vOh_Ha__view ExpandableFeedContent-module__mkQqzq__container ExpandableFeedContent-module__mkQqzq__disableFade"><div class=" useView-module__vOh_Ha__view ExpandableFeedContent-module__mkQqzq__inner"></div></div><div class=" useView-module__vOh_Ha__view EventContainer-module__w_fMqa__eventContainer"><div class=" useView-module__vOh_Ha__view index-module__DuhsOG__root" style="--useView--justify: space-between;"><div class=" useView-module__vOh_Ha__view index-module__DuhsOG__inner"><div class=" useView-module__vOh_Ha__view index-module__DuhsOG__highlightBackground" style="--useView--justify: center; --useView--align: center;"><div class=" useView-module__vOh_Ha__view"></div></div><div class=" useView-module__vOh_Ha__view index-module__DuhsOG__content" style="--useView--gap: 8px;"><div class="rendered-markdown"><div class="Markdown-module__eSbD4q__markdownTheme"><p>Replies are now much smarter and more relevant. Here's what I improved:</p>
<p><strong>Better intent detection</strong> ŌĆö expanded from 12 to 30+ message types, checked in priority order so specific cases (like <em>breakup</em>, <em>jealous</em>, <em>fight</em>, <em>late reply</em>, <em>jealousy</em>) are caught before general ones (like <em>question</em> or <em>greeting</em>). New categories include:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Emotions:</strong> angry, sad, jealous, bored, sick, fight, breakup</li>
<li><strong>Social moments:</strong> flirt, compliment, gratitude, party, good news, bad news, late reply, ignore</li>
<li><strong>Daily life:</strong> food, sleep, morning, study, busy, help, meet</li>
<li><strong>Conversation:</strong> question, greeting, agreement, disagreement, how-are-you, miss, love, sorry, thanks</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>More relevant replies</strong> ŌĆö every category now has hand-written Hinglish lines tuned to that exact context. So an angry message gets a calming/savage response, a sad message gets caring/cold ones, a question gets thoughtful/dismissive ones, a "miss you" gets sweet/snappy ones ŌĆö never generic.</p>
<p><strong>Multiple variations</strong> ŌĆö each tone has 2 variants per intent. The app picks one using a stable hash of your message, so the <em>same</em> message always gives the <em>same</em> reply, but <em>different</em> messages of the same type rotate through variants ŌĆö keeping things fresh without feeling random.</p>
<p>Try messages like:</p>
<ul>
<li><em>"Tum kal kyun nahi aaye?"</em> ŌåÆ question</li>
<li><em>"Mujhe tumse pyaar hai"</em> ŌåÆ love</li>
<li><em>"Itni der me reply?"</em> ŌåÆ late_reply</li>
<li><em>"Mai bahut udaas hu"</em> ŌåÆ sad</li>
<li><em>"Tum bahut cute lagti ho"</em> ŌåÆ flirt</li>
<li><em>"Mai aaj bahut gussa hu"</em> ŌåÆ angry</li>
</ul>
<p>Each one will give you 3 cleanly different responses.</p>
<p><strong>Next, I can add a small label above the replies showing the detected mood (e.g., "Detected: Angry message") so you know why these replies were suggested. Would you like me to do that?</strong></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=" useView-module__vOh_Ha__view EventContainer-module__w_fMqa__eventContainer"><div class=" useView-module__vOh_Ha__view" data-event-id="d7491c55-c98b-45d4-8195-bc7860cdad59" data-commit-id="21409a7a568bcd434a7424f74ae19fbdaef8a3e6" style="--useView--gap: 2px;"><div class=" useView-module__vOh_Ha__view"><button class=" useView-module__vOh_Ha__view useView-module__vOh_Ha__isHorizontal ExpandableFeedContent-module__mkQqzq__expandableButton Interactive2-module__BR3hWq__shades Interactive2-module__BR3hWq__root Interactive2-module__BR3hWq__transition Interactive2-module__BR3hWq__disabled _sdz_text _sdz_surface-bg _sdz_custom-hover:shades-up-2 _sdz_custom-pressed:shades-up-3 Interactive2-module__BR3hWq__borderRadius Interactive2-module__BR3hWq__focus" style="--useView--gap: 6px; --useView--justify: space-between; --useView--align: center; --useView--pr: 4px; --useView--pl: 4px; --Interactive2--border-radius: 12px;"><div class=" useView-module__vOh_Ha__view useView-module__vOh_Ha__isHorizontal" style="--useView--gap: 8px; --useView--align: center; --useView--grow: 1; --useView--shrink: 1;"><div class=" useView-module__vOh_Ha__view _sdz_surface-bg _sdz_surface _sdz_surface-border _sdz_surface-border-strength-subtle ToolUsePrimitives-module__A3-RwW__iconSurface" style="--useView--justify: center; --useView--align: center; --useView--pt: 4px; --useView--pr: 4px; --useView--pb: 4px; --useView--pl: 4px; --useView--border-radius: var(--border-radius-8);"><svg preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMin" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="var(--accent-positive-default)" class="Icon-module__CwnszW__icon " aria-hidden="true" style="--Icon--size: 16px; --Icon--rotate: 0deg; width: 16px; height: 16px;"><path d="M14.47 9.47a.75.75 0 1 1